Film director Umanu Ojochenemi Elijah is soaring higher after being ranked among the top breakout film directors in Nollywood in 2021. Umanu made the list, which was compiled by West Africa’s biggest film distribution outlet, Filmone Ent. Expressing happiness following the good news, the director of the blockbuster movie, ‘Devil in Agbada,’ said 2021 was a child’s play compared to what he plans to accomplish this year. He revealed that he has about four blockbuster movies due for release in 2022. According to Umanu, there is no intention of slowing down the pace as he will be shooting back-to-back movies in 2022 than ever before.   Don’t waste your life with temporary situations –…     Music industry required extra talent years back –…     Femi Adebayo inks ambassadorial deal with StarTimes   - Advertisement - Speaking further, Umanu, who is the media director of Alibaba’s January 1st concert attributed the achievements he has recorded in the movie industry to hard work and consistency. One of Africa’s most creative and decorated filmmakers, Umanu is vast in Cinematography, editing, and directing. He has an international degree in Digital storytelling from Birmingham Film Academy as well as a Cinematic filmmaking degree from the British council. He is the founder of Krystal Filmworks Limited, Nigeria’s leading production powerhouse that comprises Nollywood’s finest young filmmakers. He has been part of several Nollywood blockbuster movies including Devil in Agbada, Bitter rain, Almajiri, Call to Bar by AY Makun, LOUD the movie, The Millions, Made In Heaven, Locked, She is…, among others. He has also won notable awards and recognitions from AMVCA, AFRIFF, Best of Nollywood Award, New York Film festival, NTFF Berlin Germany, Sau Mauro film festival Italy and more.